

Varibales
Let:
a)can be updated
b)can not be redeclared

const:
a)can not be updated
b)can not be redeclared

var:
a)can be updated
b)can be redecared
c)Bad Parctice use var
d)global scope

-----------------------------------------
Object:

-> Object values are written as name : value pairs(name and value)
-> {....} with the optinal list property
-> A propert is a "key:value" psir, where a key is a string(also called property name) and there value can be anything.
-> Javascriot object from JSON object literal JSON.parse(myJSON)
->Object into string by JSON.Stringify(myJSON)
-> access object values by using (.) notation or {[]}

------------
Spread Operator (...)
-> Allow us to quickly copy all or part of an exsting array or object into another array or object
->Usage: Expanding String
Combing Arrays
Combing Object
Creating new shallow copy of Array and Object

Destructuring Assignment
->Allows to unpack values from arrays , or properties from objects
-> When desrructuring arrays, the oerdr that variables are declared is important

String Iterpolation
-> Template Literals use back-ticks(``) rather than the quotes ("") to define a string
-> With templates literals, you can use both single and double quotes inside string
->Template literals allows multiline string
->The method is called string iterpolation ${...}
-> Template literals allow expression in string
